items.content: Communities on prepaid power meters face regular disconnections amid 40 degree-plus heat, meaning no aircon, food rotting in the fridge and long, hot walks to get reconnected.

ai_summary: 65,000 customers with prepaid meters face power disconnections.
Disconnections occur due to inability to pay upfront.
Temperatures are exceeding 40 degrees Celsius in affected areas.
Customers experience no air conditioning and food spoilage.
Reconnection requires long walks in the heat.

items.standfirst: The chances of this year's contenders are reshaped as more than 23 millimetres of rain falls at Flemington on Monday. Explore our interactive form guide to all the horses set to line up in Tuesday's great race.

The interactive form guide is available for the race.
